The paper deals with dynamic graphs, which are a topic of interest in both discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of metatheorems and complexity classifications suggests a focus on theoretical computer science (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the application of the results to problems in dynamic graph theory and dynamic extensions to static problems suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
